# Fractal-AI App — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# NEVER commit .env to version control. It is gitignored.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── Claude AI (via Firebase Cloud Function proxy) ───────────────────────────
# The app routes AI calls through a Cloud Function to avoid CORS and bypass
# Firebase Hosting's 60s proxy timeout (long screenplay parses can take 90s+).
#
# To get this URL:
#   1. Deploy the Cloud Function from /functions (see functions/README.md)
#   2. Copy the trigger URL from Firebase Console → Functions → analyzeFractal
#   3. Paste it here (must end with no trailing slash)
#
# Leave BLANK to run in MOCK MODE — all AI responses are simulated locally.
# Mock mode is fast and ideal for UI development (no API costs, no cold starts).
VITE_CLAUDE_PROXY_URL=

# ─── Firebase ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required for Firestore persistence (save/load screenplays, project lobby).
# Get these from Firebase Console → Project Settings → Your apps → Web app.
#
# Without these, the app runs fully offline with no persistence.
# The demo project will still work — it lives in local Zustand state only.
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
